@230  = ~Erevain‘s Journal~
@231  = ~An excerpt...

"Tomorrow I will attempt to climb through the mountains near Kuldahar Pass.  In a way, I feel like I should help Hrothgar and the others in their investigation.  After all, they have very little protection should monsters be in the area.  Bah!  Perhaps my brothers are right.  We elves were not meant to interfere in the world of men.  These lands may once have belonged to our people, but that was long ago.  It is the territory of the wild Reghed barbarians and the Ten-Towns now.  Why resist the tide against us?  Those who do often turn to the darkness of war and conquest to reclaim the lands that we once ruled.  It is an endeavor doomed to failure.  Oh, there I go again.  Corellon help me, I‘m starting to sound like cousin Xan!"~
@232  = ~Broad Sword~
@233  = ~Erevain‘s Broad Sword +4~
@234  = ~The broad sword is a heavy military sword with a double-edged blade.  Overall sword length is about three and one-half feet, and the sword is designed mostly for cutting.  Most broad swords have a basket hilt or a shell guard.  A favored cavalry weapon, the broad sword is known in different cultures by different names, usually dependant on the hilt configuration.  The heavier blade of the broad sword makes it slightly slower and more damaging than a long sword.~
@235  = ~This sword, an oddity amonst elves who normally prefer lighter blades, the original Greycloak owner passed this owneron after years of service. Kethryllia Amaranthine reforged this sword 1221 DR for Erevain Blacksheaf's initiation to the Evereskan Greycloaks. It has since been significantly enhanced because Erevain requested this sword be heavier, more damaging and grants numerous protections. It was later redecorated to openly display the Blacksheaf family crest.

