@559  = ~Hrothgar has the air about him of a man that has seen a lot but says very little. Originally from Hillsfar, he has spent many years adventuring the length and breadth of Faerun and eventually settled in Easthaven, a small town on The Spine Of The World. In his home you see many momentos and trinkets that he has acquired from his days as an adventurer. As a fair and just man Hrothgar, quickly earned  the respect of the townsfolk and was chosen as its mayor, a job that Hrothgar took very seriously, would protect the townsfolk with his own life. It was whilst fighting a powerful demon, that Hrothgar lost his life, slain by the demon, or so rumour and legend would have you believe. The truth of what actually happened is known only to Hrothgar himself. His re-appearance a hundred years after these events is as mysterious as was his disappearance. When first you speak to Hrothgar you get a sense that you should know this burly man but the feeling passes as quickly as it came. If you ask Hrothgar about what rumour and legend say of him, he will laugh loudly and say, "So that is what the name Hrothgar has come to mean is it." You learn more of the truth as you travel together.~
