@668  = ~Ring of Might~
@669  = ~Legend says the first Ring of Might was forged by four elementalist wizards, possibly siblings. Only a dozen or so of these potent rings are said to exist. The secret of their creation, the wizards took to their graves. Nevertheless, wizards still continue to seek to discover the process.

STATISTICS:
   Armor Class Bonus: +1
   THAC0 Bonus: +1

Special Abilities:
   Charm Fire Elemental (+2 bonus to elementals saving throw)
   Charm Air Elemental (+2 bonus to elementals saving throw)
   Charm Earth Elemental (+2 bonus to elemental‘s saving throw)
   Duration: 45 seconds

Abilities when restored:
1. Dehydration:
   When activated all liquid and moisture in a 10 ft. cubic area immediately evaporates. The effect can be cast out to a range of 50 yards. Creatures can save vs.spells or die immediately. If save successful creatures suffer a loss of half total hit points. Does not effect creatures that do not possess fluids.

2. Shatter rock:
   When activated a 10 ft. cubic area of stone will shatter. The effect can be cast out to a range of 50 yards. All creatures of stone, i.e. stone golems, save vs.spells or die immediately. If save successfully creatures suffer a loss of half total hit points.

3. Solidify Air:
   When activated the air in a 10 ft.cubic area becomes solid. The effect can be cast out to a range of 50 yards. Trapped creatures can neither move nor speak and will die within 1 turn due to lack of air. Creatures can save vs.spells per round. Each round the save fails any trapped creature suffers a loss of 1 quarter total hit points until death. If save thrown successful creatures are still trapped but do not suffer the hit point loss. Creatures that do not breath air do not suffer the hit point loss but are still rendered immobile.

4.Spontaneous Combustion:
   When activated all flammable objects within a 10 ft. Cubic area bursts into flame. The effect can be cast out to a range 50 yards. The fire burns for one turn doing 10d6 damage per round to creatures trapped in the blaze. Creatures can save vs. spell each round for half damage until they die or escape the blaze. Creatures immune to fire suffer no damage.~
