@699  = ~RayVon,
           I have no exact numbers for you but you can expect many guests from across The Realms in the next couple of days. Looking to Halruaa for guidence.

                                    K.~
@700  = ~RayVon,
          Good news. Our numbers far exceed our expectations. Ulcaster cannot hope to withstand such an assault.

                                    T.~
@701  = ~RayVon,
          This will be my last missive to you. My next communication will be delivered in person when our victory is complete.

                                    T.~
@702  = ~Vrielle,
 RayVon has asked that I bring our next and final briefing forward as he wants us and the leveller to be the first wave against Ulcaster. He is hoping that with the leveller at our disposal, we will be all the force that will be needed to bring Ulcaster down. 
 He sends his apologies and ask that we preside over this meeting as a matter that needs his immediate attention has been brought to his notice by Caius... something about new students. I didn’t think Halruaa was taking in any new students until this business with Ulcaster and his damn academy had been dealt with... anyway it is imperative that Garron now be given instructions on deployment of the leveller. So Vrielle, could you please contact Brial and ask her to bring him with her. 
 Do not delay your own arrival as there is much we need to discuss before the others arrive.

                                    Sebastian.~
@703  = ~Key of the Leveller~
@704  = ~This is the key to open the cabinet to get at the Leveller.~
@705  = ~Brial,
 The time has come and RayVon wants us to be the first wave against Ulcaster. 
 Sebastian has brought forward our meeting, after which Garron will be taken to the leveller and instructed on how to deploy it. 
 You know where we are to meet, please find and bring Garron with you but do not be late yourself. If you can not contact him, then leave directions in his quarters as to where he may find us. 
	
	Vrielle.~
@706  = ~Garron,
 We have all been summoned for a final brief. The time for talking has come to an end and it is now time to put our plans into action... the leveller is ready and your hour has come Garron. 
 Sebastian has asked that you accompany me to this meeting so that you may learn how to deploy it. Against the leveller... Ulcaster shall not prevail.
 I couldn’t wait any longer for your return so I have written directions to where we are meeting. Please, for obvious reasons, don’t leave them lying around after you have read them.
 Just to the left of my room you‘ll find the secret entrance to sewers. I will unlock one of the deactivated portals there to let you enter our meeting chamber, and I hope to see you there as soon as possible.  
	
	Brial.~
@707  = ~Vrielle,
 I trust Sebastian has explained my forced absence at this brief. However this letter that I have given him to hand to you will explain further.
 Halruaa appears to have visitors who have shown more than a students interest in the academy’s affairs. Having come this far I am not about to leave anything to chance... it shouldn’t take me long to find and deal with these *inquisitive students*.
 In the meantime, I ask that as well as Garron, you also instruct Sebastian in use of the leveller. It would be good to have two persons capable of deploying it in case one or the other becomes incapacitated in any way, and as this is your project, who better than yourself to instruct them. 
 Call me over cautious if you want but I have changed the ward on the door to the room in the sewers, just in case we have been infiltrated by Ulcaster spies. I doubt spies would have cause to go down into the sewers but I still prefer to err on the side of caution. The second letter that he will give to you explains how you may open the door to the leveller. 
 If I don’t see you before you leave for Ulcaster, let me wish you luck and I will see you when you return victorious.

	RayVon.~
@708  = ~Five heads of magic schools held a meeting that was meant to start at 7:00 pm but magi being magi each arrived at a different time, one at 7:00 then 7:30, 8:30, 9:00 and finally 9:30.

1. One was a head of the *Meta* school.
2. Almeric arrived half an hour before the Transmuter.
3. Benecia arrived half an hour after the Mentalist.
4. The Conjurer arrived one and a half hours before Cherise.
5. The Invoker arrived half an hour after Dyanna who arrived after Emilius.

Go to the door and speak out loud the “name and school” of the person who arrived at the meeting at 7:30 pm.~
@709  = ~The Rawun’s Cloak~
@710  = ~This cloak once belonged to Jhadros The Rawun, the name given to the desert bards of Zakhara. Jhadros lived a contented life among the nomadic tribes of the High Desert in The Land Of Fate... that was until Fate took a hand and his sweetheart Sikayah, caught the eye of the Grand Caliph of the city of Huzuz known as *The City of Delights*. Sikayah was secreted away into the Caliph’s palace, where she was to learn the ways of life in the harem and become the old Caliph’s new wife.

Knowing that he had very little time to save Sikaya from the marriage, Jhadros travelled to the north western city of Quadib, a magical city and home to mages, sorcerers, genies and the like. There he sought out the elemental wind mage Zarad, who after one year service, fashioned this cloak for Jhadros, imbuing it with powerful magical properties.

Jhadros returned to Huzuz armed with his magical cloak and the powerful wind spells that Zarad had taught him, he entered The Great Palace on a magical Wind Carpet and whisked Sikaya away. Knowing that honour would warrant their deaths, Jhadros and his sweetheart fled  Zakhara. It isn’t known to where the lovers fled, nor their manner of escape. Some say Jhadros secured passage for them aboard a merchant ship, whilst others say they escaped aboard one of the spelljammer vessels that had been seen docked at Huzuz. 

