Despite its name, this spell does not summon dragons; rather 1D10 small whirlwind-like air elementals are conjured. A wind dragon attacks with a THAC0 of 6, has a base AC of 0, may attack once per round, and inflicts 4D4 points of damage. Any creature struck by a wind dragon will become disoriented, thus may not cast any spells in the following round.~
