@720  = ~Shadow Bolt (Illusion/Phantasm)
Level: 3
Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 1 round
Area Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: 1/2

By means of this spell, the caster brings into being a semi-real phantasm of an onrushing missile. The large, red globe-shaped illusionary projectile glows with a faerie-like radiance; it appears behind the caster and rushes at any one creature the caster concentrates upon (the caster must be able to see the target as the spell is cast).

A shadow bolt is otherwise affected only by magical barriers, not by spells or physical attacks. It inflicts 1D8 damage, plus 1 point per level of the caster. If disbelieved (the target creature makes a successful saving throw versus spells), a bolt inflicts only 1/2 damage. The strike of a shadow bolt is a considerable blow; the victim must make a strength check to avoid falling, and a successful dexterity check is required to protect exposed fragile items, otherwise, these must make saving throws vs. crushing blow to escape damage from the character‘s fall.~
@721  = ~Shatter Bones~
@722  = ~Shatter Bones (Necromancy)
Level: 6
Range: 50 yards
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area Effect: 20 yard radius
Saving Throw: None

When cast, shatter bones causes weakness in all creatures with bodies comprising of bones, including undead. This spell has no effect on creatures with incorporeal bodies, as well as creatures with elemental or metallic bodies. The effects of this spell spread outwards to a 20 yard radius. All creatures falling within the area effect of the spell suffer a -3 AC penalty, as well as a -3 penalty to attack rolls. Movement rate is halved, and affected creatures suffer 1D6 points of damage per round for the duration of this spell or until dispelled.~
@723  = ~Dweomer Warp~
@724  = ~Dweomer Warp (Alteration)
Level: 7
Range: 5 yards/2 levels
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 1 round
Area Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This insidious spell is effective against enemy spellcasters, depending on their type and level. A green ray is sent towards the target of the wizard‘s choice, enveloping the spellcaster in a field of ravaging weave-fire. Arcane magic users, wizards, bards, and sorcerers suffer 1D4 points of magic damage for half the number of levels they have. Divine magic users, clerics, druids, paladins, and rangers suffer 1D2 points of magic damage for half the number of levels they have. Warriors and other monsters that use magic as innate abilities are unaffected. Multi-/dual-class characters may suffer 1D6 points of magic damage if they are of both wizard and priest class.~
