Area Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: 1/2

This spell enables the caster to drain 3d4 hit points from any single creature and absorb them as healing energy. The caster  has three rounds after casting to touch another creature (a successful attack roll is required), or the spell is lost.

The first creature touched is affected, regardless of the caster‘s intentions. The affected creature must make a saving throw versus spells at a -2 penalty. If successful, the creature loses 1D6+1 hit points, and the caster gains no hit points. If the saving throw fails, the caster gains 3D4 hit points drained from the creature as healing energy. Morgannaver‘s sting does not confer hit points above the caster‘s normal total; excess hit points drained by the caster are lost.

The drained creature, if not killed, is wracked by intense pain for 3 rounds, suffering an Armor Class penalty of -2 and a -2 penalty to attack rolls during this time. The afflicted  creature can not cast spells nor perform other activities that require concentration. Hit points lost to this spell can be regained by the usual means of magical healing, rest, etc.~
@727  = ~Vashon‘s Shadow Bolt (Illusion/Phantasm)
Level: 3
Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 1 round
Area Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: 1/2

By means of this spell, the caster brings into being a semi-real phantasm of an onrushing missile. The large, red globe-shaped illusionary projectile glows with a faerie-like radiance; it appears behind the caster and rushes at any one creature the caster concentrates upon (the caster must be able to see the target as the spell is cast).

A shadow bolt is otherwise affected only by magical barriers, not by spells or physical attacks. It inflicts 1D8 damage, plus 1 point per level of the caster. If disbelieved (the target creature makes a successful saving throw versus spells), a bolt inflicts only 1/2 damage. The strike of a shadow bolt is a considerable blow; the victim must make a strength check to avoid falling, and a successful dexterity check is required to protect exposed fragile items, otherwise, these must make saving throws vs. crushing blow to escape damage from the character‘s fall.~
@728  = ~Summon Wind Dragons (Invocation/Evocation)
Level: 6
Range: 10 yards/level
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 6
Area Effect: 1D10 whirlwinds
Saving Throw: None

Despite its name, this spell does not summon dragons; rather 1D10 small whirlwind-like air elementals are conjured. A wind dragon attacks as a 5 Hit Dice creature (with a THAC0 of 16), has a base AC of 0, may attack once per round, and inflicts 4D4 points of damage. Any creature struck by a wind dragon will become disoriented, thus may not cast any spells in the following round.~
@729  = ~Sharia~
@730  = ~Xan‘s Eye Bite~
@731  = ~Xan‘s Eye Bite (Enchantment/Charm) 
Level 5
Range: 20 yards
Duration: 1 round/level of caster
Casting Time: 6
Area of effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Special

An *Eye Bite* spell enables the caster to merely meet the gaze of a creature and speak a single word to cause an effect. This gaze attack is in addition to any other attacks allowed to the wizard. The wizard selects one of four possible gaze attacks at the time the spell is cast, and this attack cannot be changed. Any gaze attack is negated by a successful saving throw vs. spell, with wisdom adjustments. The four effects of the spell are as follows:

Fear: The victim flees in blind terror for 1d4 rounds, after which the creature will cower or bolt for cower if confronted by the caster for 1 round/level of caster. This effect can be negated by spells that counter fear.

Charm: This effect makes the victim loyal to the caster even to the point of personal damage, otherwise it is the same as a charm monster spell. All creatures other than humans, demi-humans, and humanoid save with a +2 bonus.

Sicken: This effect causes sudden pain and fever to sweep over the victims body. Creatures with ability scores function at one-half effectiveness, others inflict only one-half damage with physical attacks. All movement rate is halved. The effect lasts for 1 round/level of the caster and can only be negated by a Remove Curse or a Dispel Magic spell. Abilities return at the rate or 1 point/round of complete rest. Creatures save same as the charm effect.

Sleep: This effect causes an individual to fall into a comatose slumber unless a successful save vs. spells is made. Creatures normally subject to a first level Sleep spell save with a -2 penalty. An effected creature must be shaken or shocked back to consciousness. Undead are immune to this effect.

Xan has modified the original Eye Bite spell to enhance it in a way that it becomes available for memorization by his students and lower level enchanters.~
