Xan has modified the original Eye Bite spell to enhance it in a way that it becomes available for memorization by his students and lower level wizards.~
@737  = ~Mass Charm~
@738  = ~Mass Charm (Enchantment/Charm)
Level: 7
Range: Special
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 6
Area of effect: Special
Saving Throw: Negative

A *Mass Charm* spell forces all creatures not allied with the caster in the area of effect to succeed at a saving throw versus spells or be charmed as if affected by the 3th level spell *Dire Charm*. Targeted creatures must be within spell range which is 20 yards + 5 yards per level of castser. Targeted creatures are subject to a negative penalty on their saving throws because of the efficiency of this spell. Any wisdom bonus against charm spells does not apply.

Undead are unaffected by this spell.~
@739  = ~Dominant (Enhanced by Xan)~
@740  = ~Properly a hat, not a helm, the Dominant is a wizardly item of impressive power.  The wizard Bemban of Immersea was known to be quite fond of these pointed hats both for their appearance and their power.  Many wizards sought their own Dominants, but their distinctive appearance soon became the butt of many jokes among adventurers.  Bemban grew senile in his later years, and left most of his fortune to private mages in the hope that they would continue to make his favorite magical hat.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities:
 Armor Class Bonus: +2
 Saving Throws Bonus: +2
 Charisma Bonus: +2
 Magic Resistance: +10%

Special Abilities:
 Memorize two additional 8th- and 9th-level spells
 Cast *Mass Charm* thrice per day
 
 A *Mass Charm* spell forces all creatures not allied with the caster in the area of effect to succeed at a saving throw versus spells or be charmed as if affected by the 3th level spell *Dire Charm*. Targeted creatures must be within spell range which is 20 yards + 5 yards per level of castser. Targeted creatures are subject to a negative penalty on their saving throws because of the efficiency of this spell. Any wisdom bonus against charm spells does not apply.
 
