 Mage (Single, Dual-, and Multi-Class)~
@741  = ~Theodoran‘s Missiles~
@742  = ~Theodoran‘s Missiles (Evocation/Invocation)
Level: 5
Range: Visual range of caster 
Duration: Instantaneous 
Casting Time: 3 
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: 1/2

When the wizard casts this spell, a narrow beam of intense heat erupts from his hands which moves towards its target, and as unerring as a Magic Missile spell. The target suffers 1d4+1 points of damage from each thermal charge, plus an additional 1d6 fire damage. The wizard gains an additional set of thermal charges for every three extra levels of experience above 10th. Victims failing their saving throws each suffer full damage from fire, but those rolling successful saving throws manage to dodge for half.~
@743  = ~Mordecai‘s Insect Swarm~
@744  = ~Mordecai‘s Insect Swarm (Conjuration/Summoning)
Level: 6
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 3 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Special

Mordecai suceeded to modify and adapt the basic fifth level spell Insect Plague cast by priests and druids for mages in a way it does twice as much damage in half the amount of time for 3 rounds + 1 round per level of the caster. This spell summons a horde of insects composed of various small beetles, spiders and other creatures. The swarm is capable of dealing devastating damage in a short period of time but is in turn fragile and easily killed. Spellcasting within the swarm is impossible. For each round the victim remains inside the swarm it must make a save vs. spells at -2 or run away in fear for one round.~
@745  = ~Wand of Mordecai's Insect Swarm~
@746  = ~These wands created by Mordecai, the Master Conjurer, are seldom seen in Faerun and highly prized by wizards. Mordecai suceeded to modify and adapt the basic fifth level spell Insect Plague cast by priests and druids for mages in a way it does twice as much damage in half the amount of time for three rounds. This wand summons a horde of insects composed of various small beetles, spiders and other creatures. The swarm is capable of dealing devastating damage in a short period of time but is in turn fragile and easily killed. Spellcasting within the swarm is impossible. For each round the victim remains inside the swarm it must make a save vs. spells at -2 or run away in fear for one round.~
