This spell surrounds the caster with an invisible barrier that moves with him. This barrier makes the wizard immune to any magical attacks, but it prevents the wizard from casting spells out of the shell.~
@763  = ~Vashon‘s Dimension Door~
@764  = ~Vashon‘s Dimension Door (Alteration, Illusion/Phantasm)
Level: 4
Range: 0
Duration: Instant 
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None 

Although being the master of illusions, Vashon has succesfully studied in the school of transmutation, and then experimented with alteration magic for a long time. His combined studies in both fields resulted in enhancing the famous Dimension Door spell in a way that the caster is able to teleport himself to any reachable, arbitrary chosen point within the same area even if it‘s not within the visual range of the caster. When the spell is cast, a dimensional portal opens up in front of the caster, which he immediately steps through. Upon passing through the portal, the caster finds himself at his chosen destination.
Unfortunately Vashon modified the scroll in a way the spell cannot be cast directly from the scroll but only learnt and memorised.~
