@969  = ~My dear Deidre,
	        I am sorry I can not be here for your visit but I have left this letter with Carialie. Regards your question of the possibility of altering a person’s race, I know of only one person wise enough to have the answer that you seek. He and I travelled extensively together in our youth and before that he had seen many wonders that I could only dream of. 
                  I recall a story he once told me that he and another were witness to. A story of a young dwarf who was unfortunate enough to fall in love with an eleven girl. This dwarf  sought far and wide for the knowledge to make himself of the elven race, and it just so happens he happened upon the sorcerer Aldruis at the same time that my friend was visiting the sorcerer himself. If the story is true, and I have no reason to doubt the word of my friend, that young dwarf left Aldruis’s abode a young sprightly elven male. 
                This friend of mine is none other than the conjurer Thalantyr, and he can be found living on the outskirts of Beregost. I can not guarantee that he will impart any of his knowledge to your gnome friend as he has become somewhat of a recluse of late and is very particular with whom he converses... some might even call him arrogant. 
                I hope this is of some use to you and please Deidre, don’t leave it so long next time between visits. Carialie and myself always look forward to and enjoy having you stay with us.

                                             Your affectionate friend
                                                              Leanaro.~
